On Fri, Jan 23, 2004 at 08:24:09AM -0800, Mark L. Hineline wrote:
> After making this Hoover modification (which is very difficult with the 
> engine in the bus -- at least, it is for the later bays, because it's 
> hard to get a wrench on both of the nuts) I decided that the right way 
> to go is to weld a piece of steel line into the tin, then clamp hose on 
> either side. That way, nothing is moving and abrading.

What I did was to take one of the electrical devices that loose wire
passes through j-boxes and the like. it has a rubber grommet that when
the nut on one end is tightened it holds the rubber hose in place.
local home improvement.

